translated: Lundström, Nils Andreas Emanuel, provincial doctor, Kållekärr, born on January 25, 1895 in Svedvi, Västmanland, son of builder Anders L. and Anna Karlsson. Married in 1934 to Annie Adèle Eklund. Children: Bo Anders Ingemar, born in 1937, Nils Göran Kristian, born in 1939. - Studied at Västerås Examination Board in 1915, obtained a Bachelor's degree in Medicine at Lund University in 1923, and a Medical License there in 1929. Worked as an assistant doctor and later a doctor at Gothenburg Women's Hospital from 1929 to 1930, at S:t Maria Hospital from 1930 to 1931. Served as a temporary provincial doctor in Tjörns, Sunnanisjö, Bjuv, Älmhult, and Pajala districts in 1931, in Sunnansjö district in 1932, as an assistant doctor at Hällefors County Hospital Surgical Department in 1932, as an acting assistant doctor at Söderköping County Hospital from 1932 to 1933, as a doctor at Östhammars County Hospital from 1933 to 1934, as an acting deputy assistant doctor at Växjö County Hospital in 1934, and as a deputy assistant doctor there from 1934 to 1936. Became the deputy and later the first deputy assistant doctor at Broby Sanatorium from 1936 to 1938. Served as a temporary provincial doctor in Åsele district in 1938, as an acting town doctor and hospital doctor in Kungsbacka in 1939, and as a provincial doctor in Tjörn district since 1942.
